description.texts.en:
Mariam is in her early 30s. She is a single mother of 4 school-going children. She is a beauty salon owner and has been in this business for 2 years. She normally opens her salon at 8:30 AM and closes at 7:00 PM. She earns profit.

This will be Mariam's 1st loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She is applying for this loan to buy a hair drying machine, hair treatments, shampoo, hair division trolley, combs and hair food. Her dream is to grow big and open another business in the near future.

Mariam will share a portion of this loan with her loan group members of Tunaweza Group Makumbusho.
name: Tunaweza Group-Makumbusho
use: to buy a hair drying machine, hair treatments, shampoo, hair division trolley, combs and hair food for her salon.

description.texts.en:
Balbina is 54 years old. She is married and has 2 adult children who are completing higher education. She lives in her own house.

With the amount of the loan, she plans to buy sewing supplies such as threads, capulanas [sarongs], and fabrics.

This is her first loan, and she plans to request another to increase her business volume.

Her dream is to finish her store where she will display her products.
description.texts.pt:
A  senhora Balbina têm  54 anos de idade, vive maritalmente, com 2 filhos maior de idade, que frequentam ensino superior, e vive na casa própria. 
Com o valor do empréstimo pretende comprar material de costura a destacar linhas, capulanas, panos.
Ė primeiro empréstimo e tem  plano de pedir outro valor para aumentar volume do seu negocio.
Têm como sonho concluir sua loja onde vai expor os seus produtos.
name: Balbina
use: to buy raw materials for sewing.

description.texts.en:
Currency formed a group called Philanthropy with the other member, Vimbai. She has a cross border trading business. She has built a house in the suburb of Westlea in Harare, Zimbabwe where she stays with her family. She is married and her husband is a self-employed mini-bus driver who transports children to school. She is 32 years old. She has three children and all of them are going to school.

After she started her business five years ago, there have been economic challenges such as the cash crisis, which affected her business. However, because of her experience and determination, her business survived. She crosses to South Africa on a monthly basis. She supplies clothes and groceries to boutiques and tuck-shops in her neighborhood.

After she managed her business very well, she experienced some growth. Now the demand for her products has increased. She needs financial support to be able to supply more. Currency used her portion of the loan to buy clothes and groceries.
name: Philanthrophy Group
use: to buy clothes and groceries.

description.texts.en:
Evelyn is 54 years old. She is single and has three children between the ages of 37 and 17. She sells groceries at Kaneshie. She has been running this business for the past 16 years.

Evelyn is a very hard-working woman and has a cheerful personality. With this loan, Evelyn will be able to open a different shop within Accra for her daughter to manage.

This is Evelyn's third time accessing a loan. She has a good loan repayment history and will be able to pay this loan without any difficulty. Thank you to Kiva lenders for supporting Evelyn’s business!
name: Evelyn
use: to buy more groceries to sell.

description.texts.en:
Fadhili is a 37-year-old married father of 2 school-going children. He works in the manufacturing sector where he makes coffins. He has been into this business for 10 good years. He usually works from 8 in the morning and closes at 6 in the evening. He earns a profit.

This will be Fadhili's 1st loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. He is applying for this loan to buy wood for making coffins, polish, nails, measuring tapes and fabrics. His dream is to grow his capital.

Fadhili will share this loan with his loan group members of "Makini Group" Lumumba.
name: Makini Group -Lumumba
use: to buy wood for making coffins, polish, nails, measuring tapes and fabrics.

description.texts.en:
This is the group called Yehowa Dzi Mila, represented by Martha, who is 36 years old. She is a hard-working married woman with three children. The group name means “Yehowa is my fire” in English.

Martha owns a shop where she has sold used clothing for the past 5 years. The group members work hard to improve their standards of living.

With the loan, Martha would like to buy more used clothing for sale. The profits from the business will be used to increase her savings and pay school fees.
name: Yehowa Dzi Mila Group
use: to buy more used clothing for sale.

description.texts.en:
Aisha is 46 years old. She is a married mother of 2 school-going children. She is a food vendor and sells different types of local foods. She has been in this business for 1 year. She usually opens her business at 6 in the morning and closes at 7 in the evening. She earns good profits that she uses to provide for her family's needs.

This will be Aisha's first loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She is applying for this loan to buy more utensils such as plates, spoons, hotpots, saucepans and flat pans, and more stock of soft drinks for her business to grow. Her dream is to improve her capital and open another business in the near future.

Aisha will share this loan with members of her loan group Maendeleo Group -Lumumba. They promise to be responsible for paying back the loan.
name: Maendeleo Group -Lumumba
use: to buy more utensils such as plates, spoons, hotpots, saucepans and flat pans, and more stock of soft drinks for her business to grow.

description.texts.en:
Sabina is 42 years old and is a married mother of 5 children who are still in school. She is a charcoal vendor and sells charcoal at retail prices. She has been operating her business for 11 years. She starts work every day at 6:30 a.m and closes at 6:45 p.m. She earns profit.

This will be Sabina's first loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She is applying for this loan to purchase sacks of charcoal and plastic bags to sell charcoal at retail prices. Her dreams is to become a big business woman in the near future.

Sabina will share a portion of this loan with the other member of her loan group Mkombozi Grp Tarime. They promise to pay back the loan.
name: Mkombozi Grp Tarime-Unit Group
use: to purchase sacks of charcoal and plastic bags to put charcoal in retail price.

description.texts.en:
Rhobi is 48 years old, a married mother of 7 children who are still in school. She is a vegetable seller. She plants and sells different vegetables from her own farm. She has been running this business for 13 years. She works everyday from 8:00 a.m and closes at 6:30 p.m. She earns a profit.

This will be Rhobi's 3rd loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. With her previous loan, she purchased axes, seeds and fertilizers. She earned profit that she used to support her family and reinvest in her business. She managed to repay the loan on time.

She is applying for this loan to buy more different vegetable seeds, fertilizer and a big knife to cut vegetables to sell. Her dream is to have a big business in the near future.

Rhobi will share a portion of this loan with her loan group, "Ujasiriamali grp Tarime". They promise to pay back the loan.
name: Ujasiriamali Grp Tarime-Unit Group
use: to buy more different vegetables seeds, fertilizer and a big knife to cut vegetables to sell.

description.texts.en:
Mary is 28 years old. She is married and blessed with 2 school-going children.

She is a retailer. She owns a retail shop that has been operational for 5 years. She opens her shop daily from 9:00 a.m. up to 10:00 p.m. She earns a good profit that she uses to cater to her family's needs.

This will be Mary's 1st loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She is applying for this loan to buy more stock of goods for her shop such as pads, diapers, toothpaste, toothbrushes, bathing soaps, washing soaps, a few utensils and stationary like pens. Her dream is to grow and open a mini-supermarket in the near future.

Mary promises to be responsible for paying back the loan.
name: Mary
use: to buy more stock of goods for a general store such as pads, diapers, toothpaste, toothbrushes, bathing soaps, washing soaps, a few utensils and stationary like pens.

description.texts.en: Christine is 38 years old and married with two children. She specializes in selling kitchenware. The client has managed to roof part of her house and feed her children with the profit from her previous loan. She wants to buy kitchenware such as plates and cups to meet the increased demand.
name: Christine
use: to buy kitchenware such as cups, dinner plates, spoons and utensils.

description.texts.en:
Innovative and forward-looking, Fredrick is also liberal-minded. He is a small-holder farmer, who lives in the Litein area of Kenya. He is blessed with lovely children, who are his greatest motivators. He perseveres because he wants to provide a better future for them.

Fredrick was unable to study to have a professional career, because of his family's economic situation. However, he never gave up and has been practicing farming for the past seven years. He has always had an affinity for farming and has even nicknamed one of his cows. He is a very proud farmer and enjoys milking his dairy cows. His cows produce 10-15 litres of milk per day. This helps him to support his family. He also grows crops, but has not been making good profits, due to poor farming inputs.

Fredrick will use the loan to pay for farm inputs to grow more crops on the farm, improve his crop production, and eventually set a good foundation for his children. Modern farming requires the use of modern techniques. Therefore, using high-quality seeds will ensure a bumper harvest and increased profit levels.

Fredrick is a visionary and his goal for the season is to boost his crop production compared to the previous year. All this can be achieved through the help and goodwill of lenders.
name: Fredrick
use: to pay for farm inputs to grow more crops on a farm in order to improve crop production and eventually set a good foundation for the children.

description.texts.en:
Josphine is a widowed woman who has always dreamt of seeing her children successfully graduate from school. Josphine works with a lot of determination so that she can achieve her dreams. On her farm, she grows crops and raises livestock. She also earns some income from a personal business. Josphine never had a formal education and is content with the farming lifestyle.

Access to modern-quality farm inputs is the pillar of agricultural revolution. However, in Kenya, a developing country, fertilizers and seeds allocated by the government is way below the needs of farmers. Since Juhudi Kilimo, which is in partnership with Kiva, ventured into the affairs of smallholder farmers in Kenya, farmers can attest that there has been a significant improvement in inputs availability than before.

Although Josphine has been earning profits through farming, not everything has been easy for this humble and industrious mother. Her farm has not been producing much of a harvest lately due to the lack of fertilizer and good seeds, and the presence of pests and diseases. That is why she is seeking a loan to buy seeds and fertilizers to improve her farming, increase her output, and, as a widowed mom, earn profits to educate her children. Josphine is very thankful for this gesture of goodwill in her life.
name: Josphine
use: to buy seeds and fertilizers to improve her farming, increase her output, and, as a widowed mom, earn profits to educate her children.

description.texts.en:
Stella, a hard working woman, represents the group called By His Grace. She is married with three children.

She design sclothing in her tailoring shop so as to meet customers' demands. Stella has been doing this business for the past 4 years.

The group members are working hard in order to improve their standards of living and with the loan, Stella would like to buy more cloth and equipment for the manufacturing of clothes for sale.

With the profits from the business she would like to reinvest into her business to improve her living standards.
name: By His Grace Group
use: to buy more cloth and equipment for the manufacturing of clothes for sale.

description.texts.en:
As the wise men say, “decisions have consequences”. Nancy made a decision to start agricultural production after searching for a job for more than five years without getting any good results. She chose not to burden her friends with her own problems and chose to venture into farming.

Nancy possesses immense knowledge, skills and experience in farming. Nancy owns a small parcel of land where she practices maize and vegetable farming and rears dairy and sheep animals. Her aspiration to get ahead is splendid because, despite her poor background status and the obstacles she has experienced, she continues her struggle to achieve.

Nancy is seeking a loan to buy seeds and expand her horticulture farming. Because of the favourable weather and road conditions, she will have an easy time transporting her horticulture products to the market.

Juhudi Kilimo facilitates loans that empower smallholder farmers like Nancy. Loans for smallholder farmers with little irregular income and no solid collateral are hard to come by in Kenya. A few organizations such as Juhudi Kilimo support farmers like Nancy. Her main dreams are to buy a house and pay for the education of her children. She really counts on your help and understanding. She kindly asks all her lenders for empowerment and support with a heart full of gratitude.
name: Nancy
use: to buy seeds to expand her horticulture farming and use the profits to fulfill her dream of supporting her children's education.

description.texts.en:
Annastacia is a modest mother who wakes up every morning at 5 o’clock to work on her farm. She is fully dedicated to her work and thinks only of progressing.

She is happily married and, together with her husband, has a lovely family. Annastacia (pictured above outside her house) resides in the Machakos area of Kenya, a remote town with harsh living conditions because of the bad terrain in the region. However, it is favourable for dairy farming.

Access to modern quality farm inputs is the pillar of agricultural revolution. However, in Kenya, a developing country, fertilizer and seed allocation by the government is way below the needs of farmers. Since Juhudi Kilimo, which is in partnership with Kiva, ventured into the affairs of smallholder farmers in Kenya, farmers can attest that there has been a significant improvement on input availability than before.

Annastacia is seeking this loan to buy farm inputs such as certified seeds and high quality fertilizers to improve her yields and generate more income to improve the quality of life for her children.

Juhudi Kilimo has partnered with Kiva to provide financial services to smallholders around Kenya. Through these financial services, farmers in Machakos now can buy productive assets and important agricultural inputs for use on their farms.
name: Annastacia
use: to buy certified seeds and high quality fertilizers to improve her yields and generate more income and improve the quality of life for her children.

description.texts.en:
Hello lenders! Beatrice is a proud, rural smallholder farmer who lives in Kitale. Kitale is famous in Kenya for its large production of maize. The residents here are very hardworking people. Beatrice works on her farm growing different varieties of crops such as bananas, maize, and some varieties of vegetables. The little income she gets is used for the sustenance of her family. She has been practicing mixed farming for the past six years. Through all of those years, she has been able to provide a daily meal for her family and a decent living.

In the modern world, agriculture requires high-quality inputs for maximum production. Beatrice is seeking a loan to purchase high-quality farm inputs that will enable her to make more profit and elevate the quality of life for her family. This loan will help Beatrice meet the increasing demand for food in the market and, in the process, generate more income to repay the loan debt. She hopes to improve the conditions of her house. Help her accomplish all her dreams with just a loan!
name: Beatrice
use: to purchase high-quality farm inputs to improve crop production so that she can make more profit and elevate her quality of life.

description.texts.en:
Deborah is a humble mom whose main dream is to improve her home's conditions. She believes that living in a third- world country where opportunities are scarce is not an excuse for her not to triumph.

Deborah is a very hardworking woman who hails from Machakos, Kenya, which is a country known worldwide for producing athletes who have broken world records in major marathons: the athletic “creme de la crème." Deborah earns her primary income by raising crops and animal farming. She also earns some income through a personal business.

Access to modern-quality farm inputs is the pillar of agricultural revolution. However, in Kenya, a developing country, fertilizer and seed allocation by the government is way below the needs of farmers. Since Juhudi Kilimo, which is in partnership with Kiva, ventured into the affairs of smallholder farmers in Kenya, farmers can attest that there has been a significant improvement on input availability compared to before.

Deborah is seeking a 40,000 KES loan through Kiva's field partner, Juhudi Kilimo. She will use it to buy farm inputs, such as fertilizer and seed, to enable her to grow more vegetables, reap maximum profits, and increase her business.

She is always working to improve her family’s living conditions, but her biggest dreams are to become independent, support her parents and children by herself, and buy a home. Deborah is very thankful to lenders in advance.
name: Deborah
use: to buy farming inputs such as fertilizer and seed, to enable her to grow more vegetables, reap maximum profits, and increase her business.

description.texts.en:
Selestina, in her mid 30's, is a married mother of three children of the ages 13, 10 and 7. They are school aged.

She is a green grocer. She has been in this business for two years. She usually opens her business at 9:00 am and closes at 8:00 pm. Her business is doing good and she earns a profit.

This will be Selestina's first loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She is applying for this loan to buy more stock of tomatoes, onions, garlic, ginger, green vegetables and seasonal fruits. Her dream is to grow her business more than now.

Selestina will share this loan with her loan group members of Tunaweza Group - Makumbusho.
name: Tunaweza Group-Makumbusho
use: to buy more stock of tomatoes, onions, garlic, ginger, green vegetables and seasonal fruits.

description.texts.en: Moses is a married man who supports his family. He runs a transport business to meet his daily family needs. His business has been growing and he intends to use the loan to expand his business to meet demand. It is his first loan and he intends to pay back the loan from the profits of his business. His business has enabled him to create employment for others and he dreams of becoming a successful business man one day.
name: Moses Muranga
use: to expand a motorcycle business buy buying a new motorcycle.

description.texts.en:
Get to know Beatrice (pictured above, alongside her husband). Beatrice is 53 years old. She is very clear and straightforward about what she wants in life, which is to give her family a good quality life. She lives in a poor, rural village in Kitale.

Beatrice started farming due to economic necessity. She also earns some income from a personal business. The biggest constraint to Beatrice’s success is the use of poor-quality farm inputs.

Unlike most microfinance organizations in Kenya that have imposed very complicated procedures in funds acquisition, thereby discouraging smallholder farmers, Juhudi Kilimo is working closely with Kiva to make loan acquisition for a smallholder farmer easy and convenient. Through this intervention, movement of funds in the rural communities has increased, thereby alleviating rural poverty.

Beatrice is seeking this loan to purchase high-quality farm inputs to increase her productivity, make more profits, and use funds to pay school fees for her children. This loan is, therefore, an opportunity that she never got before. Her irregular income and lack of collateral security were the main drawbacks, limiting her from accessing a loan in commercial banks.

Thanks to Juhudi Kilimo and Kiva, the life of Beatrice and her family will be changed through this loan.
name: Beatrice
use: to purchase high-quality farm inputs to increase her productivity, make more profits, and use funds to pay school fees for her children.

description.texts.en:
After finishing at the Teachers College in July 2017, Lindleen could not find a place to teach so she started a poultry business at home. She built a nice fowl run with a capacity of 350 birds and started with a batch of 50 broilers. This was in a bid to contribute to the household income and take care of their four children, three of whom are in school. She is happily married to a self-employed carpenter.

From time to time, her profits used to be affected by high mortality but this could not weigh her down as she strongly believe that every downfall in business begets additional experience. Lindleen sells her broilers at Makoni shopping centre. With that, she managed to secure prominent clients who are looking for greater supply. Thus, Lindleen’s capital was becoming inadequate for her to satisfy all her clients. When she heard of Thrive Microfinance, Lindleen applied for a loan to buy an extra 100 birds.
name: Lindleen Group
use: to increase the number of birds per batch.

description.texts.en:
Early every morning, when the birds and crickets are chanting their sweet melodies to give way to the new sun, Christine jumps out of bed and prepares for a busy day. She prepares her children for school and later moves to her farm. This is the daily life of Christine who works tirelessly to steward her family and to establish a successful agribusiness farm.

Christine practices animal (cows and sheep) and crop farming (horticulture). Waste from her animals is usually composted and used to increase soil fertility in her farm. Thanks to her perseverance, her children can have at least two meals in a single day.

Unlike most microfinance businesses in Kenya that have imposed very complicated procedures in funds acquisition thereby discouraging smallholder farmers, Juhudi Kilimo is working closely with Kiva to make loan acquisition for a smallholder farmer easy and convenient. Through this intervention, movement of funds in the rural communities has increased thereby alleviating rural poverty.

The Eldoret area, where Christine farms, has favourable conditions for horticulture farming, which is why Christine is seeking a loan to buy seeds so that she can expand her horticulture farming. Due to the good roads, good climate, and a good transportation network, she is sure that she will reap maximum profits and be able to increase her business. Christine is very thankful in advance for your help and contribution. She is looking forward to your warm response.
name: Christine
use: to buy seeds so that she can expand her horticulture farming, satisfy the ready market for horticulture products and improve her family's living conditions.

description.texts.en:
As a positive thinker, Mary has always seen possibilities in her life. She is one of the most hardworking women on planet Earth. Mary resides in a remote village in the Kerugoya area of Kenya and her primary sources of income are crop and animal farming. She is content with the farming way of life.

Mary is a smallholder farmer who is characterized by her sense of responsibility and self-sacrifice, and her love for her work, her land and her family. She is a person who has had to overcome a lot of adversity in her life, however, she has always had the strength to overcome it and move forward with her children.

The Kerugoya area has favorable conditions for horticulture farming. That is why Mary is seeking a loan to buy seeds to start a horticulture farming business. Because of good roads, a good climate, and a good transportation network, she is sure that she will reap maximum profits and be able to increase her business, helping her to support her children and aging parents.

Being a smallholder woman farmer, accessing credit facilities in Kenya is very challenging, but Mary feels relieved knowing there are institutions such as Kiva that help hardworking women like her.

Please help Mary so that her horticulture farming business can flourish.
name: Mary
use: to buy seeds to start a horticulture farming business.

description.texts.en:
Juhudi Kilimo is celebrating hardworking mothers such as Annah who reside in the Matuu area of Kenya.

Annah is a determined mother who has only one thought on her mind: to prosper. She is responsible for all the operations on her farm, which she does perfectly. On her farm, she rears dairy cows and poultry, grows crops, and she also carries out daily household chores such as cooking, collecting water, and caring for the children.

She has been working in agriculture for 9 years now. She makes money selling produce from her farm, including milk, eggs and crops. She enjoys plowing her farm and watering her plants. Crop diseases pose a big challenge for her as does poor productivity.

Annah is seeking an emergency loan to buy good-quality seeds and fertilizer, which will help increase soil fertility and productivity on her farm. Increased productivity will allow her to improve her quality of life and her living standard. Through training from Juhudi Kilimo, she has learned about the culture of saving, and she plans to use the increased income to improve her farming.

This loan will go a long way in changing the lives of Annah and her family members. Annah dreams of building a modern house where her family can have an amazing quality of life.

Kindly lend to a woman smallholder farmer !
name: Annah
use: to buy good-quality seeds and fertilizer, which will help a mom increase soil fertility and productivity on her farm.

description.texts.en:
Hello, Kiva community!

Get to know Milkah. She is an inspiring single mother from Kerugoya, in the central region of Kenya, where she lives with her children. Milkah started farming nine years ago with an aim of providing for the basic needs of her family. She has done tremendous work in the field of agribusiness with her great passion and enthusiasm. The results of her determination are the smiling faces of her children when they wake up early every day to go to school.

Although she makes profit from farming, Milkah is not comfortable and has always wanted to increase her income by buying seeds to plant and sell the resulting crops. So she is seeking this loan to buy farm inputs such as certified seeds and nutrient-rich fertilizers to improve her horticultural farming. Milkah’s remote area has a high demand for food, which means she could both increase her profits and satisfy the demand for horticulture products.

Milkah feels relieved because Juhudi Kilimo is partnering with wonderful Kiva lenders to help hardworking and honest women farmers turn their dreams into reality. Milkah believes that this loan will help. Kindly lend to her!
name: Milkah
use: to buy seeds to start horticultural farming, make profits, and, as a single woman, improve her living conditions and secure her children's future.

description.texts.en:
Farming in Kerugoya sometimes becomes a struggle beyond imagination, especially due to unpredictable weather and changing market trends.

Mary is one of the most hardworking women farmers in Kerugoya. She is happily married, and she and her hubby are blessed with lovely children, so she is a farmer and a mother to very beautiful children. Her primary source of income is milk, and she also plants maize on her farm. Mary loves and enjoys farming for it is her only way of providing a meal for her family.

As the Kerugoya area is a favorable one for farming, she is seeking a 30,000 KES loan through Kiva's field partner Juhudi Kilimo. She will use it to buy farm inputs, such as fertilizer and seeds, to enable her to grow more vegetables, reap maximum profits, and increase her business.

Being a woman and accessing funds in Kenya, especially around her village, is very challenging. Mary is relieved knowing there are institutions like Kiva that help enterprising women like her. She is always working to improve her family’s living conditions, but her biggest dreams are to become independent and support her family by herself, to secure her children’s future by paying tuition fees, and to buy a home.
name: Mary
use: to buy farm inputs such as fertilizer and seeds to enable her to grow more vegetables, reap maximum profits, and increase her business.

description.texts.en: Phanic is 28 years old. She is married with one child. She has had a boutique business for seven years. She will be using the loan to purchase more stock of clothes and hopes this will help her to save money for future use. Her hopes and dreams for the future are to build her family a modern house.
name: Phanic
use: to purchase more stock of clothes for her store.

description.texts.en: Luka is 42 years old. He is married with five children. He has had an animal sales business for six years. He will be using the loan to purchase more animals for resale at a later stage, and he hopes this will help him pay fees for his children with profits made. His hopes and dreams for the future are to build a better house for his family.
name: Luka
use: to purchase more animals for resale at a later stage.

description.texts.en:
Caroline is a mom who was born in a humble family. She lives in a post-election conflict area where insecurity and high poverty levels have affected the community a lot. Although she has gone through all these challenges, she has come out triumphant.

Caroline is very hardworking and a go-getter. She hails from a remote village in the Kerugoya area of Kenya. Her primary sources of income are crops and animal farming. She also earns some income through a personal business. Caroline is content with the farming way of life. Caroline is a very enterprising woman, and although she never had formal education or formal employment, she has always worked hard on her farm and she has always ensured her children and family can have a decent meal.

The Kerugoya area has favourable conditions for horticulture farming, and that is why Caroline is seeking a loan to buy seeds and start a horticulture farming business. With good roads, a good climate, and a good transportation network, she is sure that she will reap maximum profits and be able to increase her business. Horticulture produce such as vegetables require good climate and a good transport network because they are perishable. Caroline believes that this investment will bring profits, grow her business, and allow her to generate more income to fulfill her dreams of making some home improvements. Her goal is to give her family the best life possible.
name: Caroline
use: to buy seeds to start a horticulture farming business to provide a better living for the children.

description.texts.en:
Before Evans took on farming, he had to understand the risks involved in nurturing the growth of crops and keeping of farm animals. He is a married man who loves his family and spends a considerable amount of time taking care of his family as well as his farm, which sometimes becomes very tedious and tiresome. In the modern world, agriculture has become exceedingly dynamic, therefore, making the kind of inputs that are being used in the sector today necessary. On this note, there is a need to use improved farming inputs for effective production. These include high quality seeds, and nutrient-rich fertilizer. Evans wants to purchase farming inputs such as fertilizer and hybrid seeds to boost the quality of his horticulture produce, earn more profits, and elevate his living standards.

It is challenging for a smallholder farmer to access funds in Kenya, especially around his village. Evans was relieved to find that there are institutions such as Kiva that helps enterprising farmers like him. He is always working to improve his family’s living conditions and his biggest dreams are to become independent and support his family by himself, secure his grandchildren’s future, and to buy a modern home.
name: Evans
use: to purchase farming inputs such as fertilizer and hybrid seeds to boost the quality of his horticulture produce, earn more profits, and elevate his living standards.

description.texts.en:
Dear special people,

Lilian is a hard-working woman who has a huge heart for farming. In addition, her humility, decency, and wisdom differentiate her from other farmers in the Kitale area of Kenya. She is blessed with lovely children, who are her greatest motivators. She perseveres because she wants to provide a better future for them. Lilian loves farming. She has even nicknamed one of her cows and is a very proud farmer, especially when she is milking her cows. Her cows produce 8-9 liters per day, which helps her support her family.

Lilian also practices crop farming, but she has not been making good profits because of poor farming inputs. She is seeking a loan to buy farm inputs. Through the loan, she will be able to purchase high-quality seeds and fertilizers that she will use to greatly improve her crop production. Modern farming requires the use of modern techniques, and high-quality seeds will assure that she has a bumper harvest and generates increased profits.

Lilian is very visionary, and her goal for this season is to boost her crop production. All of this can be achieved through lenders’ help and goodwill. Make a $25 loan or more, and push Lilian’s dream closer to reality!
name: Lilian
use: to purchase high-quality seeds and fertilizers that she will use to greatly improve her crop production.

description.texts.en:
Meet Stella, a humble mother. Stella is a hardworking, female farmer who tries her best to have a rich and prosperous farm. She is very clear about what she wants in life and is determined to get ahead and have a good life.

Stella is a smallholder farmer from Nkubu in the central region of Kenya. She owns a small parcel of farmland. On the farm, she practices mixed farming. This mother keeps dairy animals and poultry and grows maize and vegetables. She has 10 years of experience in farming.

Stella is seeking a loan to buy seeds and expand her horticulture farm. Because of the favourable weather and road conditions, she will have an easy time transporting her horticulture products to the market. Loans for smallholder farmers with little, irregular income and no solid collateral are hard to come by in Kenya. A few organizations such as Juhudi Kilimo support farmers like Stella.

Juhudi Kilimo facilitates loans that empower smallholder farmers like Stella. Her main dreams are to buy a house and pay for the education of her children. She really counts on your help and understanding. She kindly asks all her lenders for empowerment and support with a heart full of gratitude.
name: Stella
use: to buy seeds to expand her horticulture farming, and as a single woman, use the profits to support her children by paying tuition fees, as they report to school this month.

description.texts.en:
Sara is a hardworking woman who moved from the gutter to incredible heights through farming. Sara enjoys farming as a way of giving her family a healthy lifestyle. She is hardworking and very enterprising. Sara has been in the farming business for the last seven years. She says farming is the best activity she has ever engaged in.

In Kenya, agriculture is one of the most competitive industries, especially due to the high costs of operations necessary to improve farming. Such costs include the cost of land acquisition, and inputs (which have skyrocketed). To meet the high costs of inputs, farmers have been forced to borrow from financial institutions, which sometimes impose very complicated procedures in loan distribution. Some farmers, especially women, end up in hopelessness, despondency, and lack the morale to invest in agriculture.

Sara learned that Juhudi Kilimo has intervened in the activities of rural small farmers by giving them financial support in the form of loans. This enables farmers to access income-generating assets, as well as farming inputs. Sara has used this loan to purchase farming inputs such as fertilizers and hybrid seeds to boost the quality of her produce, earn more profits, and elevate her living standards. Please lend to this industrious woman so that she can save for her children's education.
name: Sara
use: to purchase farming inputs, such as fertilizers and hybrid seeds, to boost the quality of her produce, earn more profits, and elevate her living standards.

description.texts.en:
As the only voice of hope that her children have, Mary stands strong. She is determined to break the chains of poverty that have formed a cycle in her family. Mary, a single mum, has a great history of valor, perseverance, and courage in farming.

Her primary sources of income have been milk, eggs, crops, and some small business ventures (cereal trading) that help her make ends meet. She is determined and is very focused on her goals and dreams.

She is seeking a loan to stock her cereals business. She plans to use the money to purchase different cereals such as lentils, cowpeas, maize, beans, and sorghum. She will transport cereals in bulk to faraway markets, where she will sell at prices high enough to meet all the expenses incurred plus profit. She is confident that she will be able to repay the loan on time because she is hardworking and financially disciplined.

Returns from the investment will change her life, as she will use the additional income to raise her family's living standards and pay for her children's education. Her positive attitude and her hopes of getting ahead show that Mary has an immense desire to better herself and, of course, a desire to receive a favourable response to her loan request.

Support her during this second quarter of 2018!
name: Mary
use: to purchase different cereals such as lentils, cowpeas, maize, beans, and sorghum to resell, and as a single woman, support her children.

borrowers: [{'first_name': ' Rose  ', 'last_name': '', 'gender': 'F', 'pictured': True}, {'first_name': 'Catherine  ', 'last_name': '', 'gender': 'F', 'pictured': True}, {'first_name': 'Adrine', 'last_name': '', 'gender': 'F', 'pictured': True}, {'first_name': ' Allen  ', 'last_name': '', 'gender': 'F', 'pictured': True}, {'first_name': ' Rosemary  ', 'last_name': '', 'gender': 'F', 'pictured': True}]
description.texts.en:
This is the Omugyenyi Tumanyane Group located in Ntungamo. It consists of five women who defied depending entirely on their husbands for everything. The members engage in various economic activities with an objective of poverty eradication.

Rose, age 40, is a married woman with four children who attend school. She operates a retail shop in a small trading centre. She started this business a few years ago to help her husband with the family expenses and also develop herself.

In a bid to facilitate further growth, Rose has applied for a loan from UGAFODE to buy more stock for her retail shop. She is confident that her sales will increase due to the fact that a fully stocked shop attracts customers as opposed to a shop with empty shelves. This will provide her with more income to improve her family's standard of living and also keep her children in school.

Rose and the other group members send their sincere gratitude to the funders for the financial support that will boost their businesses.
name: Omungyenyi Tumanyane Group
use: to buy more stock for her shop.

description.texts.en:
George is married with school-going children. He lives in Rukungiri with his family. George operates a shop that sells electronics which has been his main source of income for the past years. In holidays, he trades in fish as the children and the wife help out in the shop. The extra income he gets from selling fish supplements the family income.

George submits that his sales are declining due to the limited stock which has greatly lowered his income. This has made it really hard for him to provide for his family due to the fact that the electronics shop is the family's main source of income.

In a bid to boost his business, George has applied for a loan of 2,600,000 UGX from UGAFODE to add more stock of the highly demanded items like chargers, phone jackets, adapters and solar panels in the shop. He is confident that the increase in stock will influence an increase in the sales, and so will his income.

George appreciates the funders for the financial support that will boost his business. His dream is to further expand his retail shop to a wholesale outlet supermarket and he is working hard towards making it happen.
name: George
use: to add stock in his retail shop.

description.texts.en:
Meet Emmah, a young farmer with an infectious smile. She is from a remote village in Bungoma, Kenya. She has defied the common thinking among most Kenyans that agriculture is only for the older generation.

Emmah is a mom who is blessed with lovely children. Her primary source of income is from milk, and she plants different varieties of food crops. Her husband uses their motorbike to transport produce to the local market. She also engages in a personal business and has been able to earn a handsome profit. Emmah practices agriculture with a difference by employing youthful energy, hard work, and knowledge from many agricultural training seminars with Juhudi Kilimo.

Emmah is seeking a loan to buy cereals so that she can increase her profits and satisfy the existing demand. Accessing funds has been a challenge, but she feels relieved knowing Juhudi Kilimo, partnered with Kiva lenders, helps hardworking women farmers turn dreams into reality through training and loan financing.

Emmah believes that this loan will benefit her greatly, that she will be able to satisfy the demand for cereals, and that the extra income will change her life and increase her business. Increased profits will allow Emmah to repay this loan and provide a secure future for her school-going children.
name: Emmah
use: to buy high-demand cereals, such as cow peas, lentils, rice and maize to resell and help a zealous mom secure the lives of her school-going children.

description.texts.en:
Kennedy believes in the doctrine of hard work. He also believes that hard work is the most important weapon one can use to end poverty in life.

Kennedy is a father and a rural smallholder farmer from the Kitale area of Kenya. His main income sources are milk from his dairy farm and a small personal business. However, he is also involved in other agricultural activities such as growing tea, vegetables, fruits, and grains.

One objective that Juhudi Kilimo aims at fulfilling is increasing the ease of accessing farm inputs and income-generating assets for farmers. Through the intervention of Juhudi Kilimo and Kiva, inputs such as fertilizers and pesticides have become more accessible to its members than buying a bottle of water.

Kennedy is seeking a loan to pay for farm inputs such as quality fertilizers and hybrid seeds to help improve his horticulture farm. This intervention will help him meet the increasing demand for food in the market and, in the process, generate more income to repay the loan debt and improve his family's quality of life.

Please help this farmer to accomplish all his dreams by giving him a loan!
name: Kennedy
use: to pay the school fees for her children, to enable them to learn smoothly for a brighter future.

description.texts.en:
Violet is a rural smallholder farmer from the Kitale area of Kenya and is the mother of lovely children. Violet is married to a fellow farmer. Her family's main sources of income are horticulture and milk from their dairy farm. They are also involved in other agricultural activities such as growing bananas, vegetables, fruits and grains.

The biggest problem that farmers from her remote village face is the huge deficit in terms of access to agricultural inputs, meaning that the farmers' yields and incomes are far below what they could be.

Juhudi Kilimo partnered with Kiva to provide financial services to smallholders around Kenya. Through these financial services, farmers from her remote village, like Violet, can now buy productive assets and important agricultural inputs for use on their farms.

Violet is seeking a loan to buy farm inputs such as seeds and fertilizer to improve her horticulture farm.

Your loan will enable her to improve her production. This intervention will help her fill the increasing demand for food in the market and, in the process, generate more income to repay the loan debt and improve the quality of life for her family. She also hopes to improve the condition of her house.

Help this mother accomplish all her dreams with just one loan!
name: Violet
use: to buy farm inputs such as seeds and fertilizer to improve her horticulture farm.

description.texts.en:
7uGreetings from Nkubu, Kenya!

This is Ruth, a 32-year-old single mother who is a picture of beauty and has a captivating smile. Ruth is the true definition of a hard worker and a happy mother. She is a farmer in Nkubu, an area endowed with natural streams. Ruth grows maize, raises poultry, and engages in dairy farming. She produces milk and eggs for commercial purposes as opposed to many rural farmers who produce for subsistence.

Ruth also grows maize for food and sales. These commercial activities place her in a better position to engage in other agricultural businesses, which she does. Access to modern, quality farm inputs is the pillar of agricultural revolution. However, in Kenya, a developing country, fertilizers and seed allocation by the government is way below the needs of farmers. Since Juhudi Kilimo which is in partnership with Kiva, ventured in the affairs of smallholder farmers in Kenya, farmers can attest that there has been a significant improvement on inputs availability than were previously available. Ruth is seeking a loan to buy farm inputs such as certified seeds and nutrient-rich fertilizers. Your loan will enable her to improve her production through the use of quality farm inputs. Through this intervention, she will be able to improve the quality of her farm products and attract more buyers, leading to more profits.
name: Ruth
use: to buy farm inputs such as certified seeds and nutrient-rich fertilizers and, as a hardworking single mother, to support her children.

description.texts.en:
Griffin is a married man. He has 2 children. He describes himself as God-fearing. He operates a transportation business where he transports customers from one point to another using his motorcycle. He also engages in dairy farming.

He has been involved in this business for 6 years. His business is located in a good area and his primary customers are locals. He describes his biggest business challenge to be inadequate working capital.

He will use the Kes 80,000 loan to purchase a cow and animal feed. This is his third loan with SMEP Microfinance Bank. Previous loans were repaid successfully.
name: Griffin
use: to purchase a cow and animal feeds.

description.texts.en:
Rophence is a Kiva borrower who describes herself as determined. She operates an Mpesa services shop where she offers money transfer services. She has been involved in this business for 2 years.

Rophence's business is located in a good area and her primary customers are locals. She describes her biggest business challenge to be inadequate working capital.She will use the 80,000 KES loan to add more float of money to enable her carry out numerous transactions.

Her business goal is to be a super agent in the future. She will use the anticipated profits to purchase additional stock of airtime and other items.
name: Rophence
use: to add more float of money to enable her carry out numerous transactions.

description.texts.en: Martha is a married woman. She describes herself as determined. She operates a farm, where she grows potatoes, maize, beans, and other crops. She has been involved in this business for over three years. Her business is located in a fertile area, and her customers are primarily locals. She says her biggest business challenge is inadequate working capital. She will use the KES 60,000 loan to buy farm inputs, to boost production. She will use the anticipated profits to pay school fees.
name: Martha
use: to buy farm inputs to boost production.

description.texts.en:
Hello Kiva Community!

Meet Rose, who is a crop and animal farmer, and a mother eager to provide the very best for her family. She states that with her small income, she hasn’t been able to provide sufficient lighting through the electricity in her home. Her family has been using kerosene lamps, despite the toxic fumes that put the family at risk of contracting respiratory diseases.

Rose is kindly appealing for a loan to buy a solar lantern to provide adequate lighting, enabling her children to read well while at home. With the lantern’s dual charging capability, her husband will also be able to efficiently charge his phone. Kindly consider lending to her.
name: Rose
use: to buy a solar lantern.

description.texts.en:
As a poor mother, Adelaide has been through many adversities, but she always triumphs.

She is a smallholder farmer full of dreams and aspirations in her life. She resides in a remote village in the lush hills of Kitale, in the Rift Valley region of Kenya.

As the key breadwinner of her family, Adelaide has been practicing mixed farming for the past nine years. Because of the immense knowledge she has of farming, she commands a lot of respect from other farmers in her village.

Adelaide’s primary source of income has been milk, eggs, and crops. She also engages in a small business to supplement the meager income she earns through farming.

Although she has been making profits from farming, she has identified a market segment for selling cereals. The only big challenge she faces is the lack of funds.

Adelaide is requesting a loan to buy cereals. She intends to buy different varieties of cereals, such as lentils, cow peas, rice, and wheat, to sell in the local market.

The market for cereals is never a problem because the demand is always high and she plans to take advantage of that. Because of the good relationship she has with her neighbors, she plans to increase her market by using word-of-mouth to reach more customers and markets.

You can help this woman achieve her dreams with this loan, which will surely bring big profits.

Light up a spirit this month!
name: Adelaide
use: to buy cereals (e.g., lentils, cow peas, and maize) to sell, so this hard-working mother can improve her income and be better able to support her family.

description.texts.en:
John is 36 years old and lives in Chorkor. He has lived in Chorkor for some years now. Originally, he is from Accra. John has three children who are all schooling. He is applying for a loan portion to buy more bags to sell.

His dream for the future is to expand his business to buy and sell cloths and bags wholesale.

He and his counterpart would like to thank all of his Kiva lenders for their generosity and support.
name: Biakoye Group
use: to buy and sell clothes and bags wholesale.

description.texts.en:
Auwulu is from a small community in Kaduna state where he grows maize to support his family. Auwulu has been a Babban Gona member for one season and, as a result, he has been able to send two children to a better school with the profits from his farm.

Auwulu’s goal for this farming season is to learn new agronomic practices. With this loan, he will get access to improved seeds, fertilizers, herbicides and other inputs that are critical to increasing his yield to up to 4.2 metric tonnes per hectare, which is more than double the national average in Nigeria. This will enable him generate earnings of up to four times the average Nigerian farmer’s annual income.

Auwulu recalls sending his children to school as his happiest memory as a Babban Gona member. Auwulu looks forward to a brighter future with Babban Gona and to making many more great memories with his family.
name: Auwulu
use: to purchase improved inputs to get a good yield and enhance living standards.

description.texts.en:
Rosemary is 43 years old, married and blessed with five children. She makes and sells liquid detergents as well as practices farming, which she has done for 11 years.

This is Rosemary's second loan, which she will use to buy ingredients to make liquid washing detergents. She will use the profits from the expanded business to educate and provide basic needs like food, clothing, medical care and education for her children, as well as service the loan.

Rosemary's hopes and dreams are to build a strong business, improve her family’s standard of living and provide her children with the best education.
name: Rosemary
use: to buy ingredients to make liquid washing detergents.

description.texts.en:
Jacob is 47 years old. He is married and blessed with eight children. His business is farming, which he has done for four years.

This is his second loan and he will use it to buy seeds and fertilizers to improve farm yield as well as diversify into a retail shop to vary sources of income. He will use the profits from his expanded business to provide for his family's basic needs.

His hopes and dreams are to have a stable business and a strong, happy family.
name: Jacob
use: to buy seeds and fertilizers to improve farm yield as well as diversify into a retail shop to vary sources of income.

description.texts.en:
Moshi is 50 years old, married, and blessed with six children, all of whom are still in school. A food vendor for seven years, she sells local foods and bites, She normally opens her business for 6:00 a.m. and closes at 10:00 p.m. daily. She earns profit.

This will be Moshi's second loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. With her previous loan, she bought a variety of utensils and tables, using her profits to support her family, reinvest in her business and repay the loan.

Moshi will use this loan to buy food items such as kilos of maize flour, wheat flour, cooking oil, other ingredients and charcoal. Her dreams is to open a soft drinks shop someday.

Moshi will share a portion of this loan with her loan group members of Ujamaa-Shinyanga, whose members promise to pay back the loan in a timely fashion.
name: Ujamaa-Shinyanga Group
use: to food items such as kilos of maize flour, wheat flour, cooking oil, other ingredients and charcoal.

description.texts.en:
Sama'ila is from a small community in Kaduna state where he grows maize to support his family. Sama'ila has been a Babban Gona member for one season and as a result, he has been able to send three children to a better school with the profits from his farm.

Sama'ila’s goal for this farming season is to be the best performing farmer in his community. With this loan, he will get access to improved seed, fertilizers, herbicides and other inputs which are critical to increasing his yield to up to 4.2 metric tonnes per hectare, which is more than double the national average in Nigeria. This will enable him to generate earnings of up to four times the average Nigerian farmer’s annual income

Sama'ila recalls building a better house for his family as his happiest memory as a Babban Gona member. Sama'ila looks forward to a brighter future with Babban Gona and to making many more great memories with his family.
name: Sama'ila
use: to purchase improved inputs in order to get a good harvest and enhance living standards.

description.texts.en:
This is a micro business group located in a Kampala surburb. It consists of women and men who are in small scale business as their main source of income. The members formed this group to provide each other with support in terms of finances and business advice with a common goal of poverty eradication.

Gladys, aged 38, is married with four children aged 14, 10, 8 and 6 years old respectively and all are attending school. Just like other group members, she is also a business lady dealing in retail items in Kiwenda, a business which sustains her family. She started as a shop attendant but through hard work, she saved up money which she used to start up her own business. The demand for her products, especially beverages and groceries, has increased with the opening of a garage nearby.

Gladys has applied for a loan from UGAFODE to buy more stock for her shop. She is hopeful that it will trigger an increase in sales, thus bringing in more returns. She is grateful for the support that will boost her business and also transform her family's standard of living. Gladys is described as a good leader by her fellow group colleagues since she chairs the group.
name: Kiwenda Group,gayaza.
use: to restock her retail shop.

description.texts.en:
This is Karambi Abamwe group located in the outskirts of Ntungamo. It consists of five women who engage in farming as their source of income.

Joy (extreme right)is a married woman with five children who attend school. She engages in both crop farming and livestock farming. She mainly gets her income from selling milk and bananas.

She has continuously cropped on the same land over the years, which has caused loss of soil fertility. There has been reduction in crop production, which has led to low harvests, thus bringing in low returns. Joy submits that this has reduced her finances, which has made it hard for her to provide for her family, since farming is her only source of income.

In a bid to improve her farming, she has approached UGAFODE for a loan to buy fertilizers for her garden. She is confident that her farm yields will improve both in quality and quantity, thus bringing in more returns.

Joy and the other group members extend their gratitude to the funders for the financial support that will transform their lives and families.
name: Karambi Abamwe Group
use: to buy fertilizers for her banana plantation.

description.texts.en:
Rose is a woman with big dreams. She is blessed with cute children. Her perseverance and determination to improve her family's quality of life have enabled her to be a successful farmer.

Rose ventured into farming eight years ago. Her primary income sources are horticultural crops and animal products. Rose enjoys her farming business mostly because it gives her a sense of independence. She spends a lot of time plowing her land and looking after animals.

Rose is humbly pleading and seeking a loan of KES 40,000 to buy farm inputs to expand her horticultural farm. By scaling up the business, she will reduce production costs and increase output.

Rose is a very hardworking smallhold farmer who has set targets for herself. Her strategy is to double her production and maximize her profits. If Rose makes a surplus, she plans to put the profits back into the business so that the production cycle will continue.

Through the loan, she will provide safe food in her house and also improve her living conditions.

Kindly be inspired and lend to her!
name: Rose
use: to buy farming inputs and expand a horticultural farm in order to make more profits and provide food for the children.

description.texts.en:
Rodah is 40 years old. She is married, with two children. She has had a livestock farming business for 10 years.

She will be using the loan to purchase a number of cows and sheep to rear and sell later at a profit and hopes to use the anticipated profits to provide for her family's basic needs.

Her hopes and dreams for the future are to improve her life.
name: Roddah
use: to purchase a number of cows and sheep.

description.texts.en:
Pius is 33 years old, married, and blessed with one child. His business is a motorcycle taxi, which he has operated for six years.

Pius will use this, his first loan, to purchase spare parts for his motorcycle taxi. He will use subsequent profits from expanded business to provide basic needs such as food and clothing for his family and educate his children.

Pius' hopes and dreams are to have a good life and give a good education to his children.
name: Pius
use: to purchase spare parts for his motorcycle taxi.

description.texts.en:
Alice is 38 years old. She is married and blessed with two children. She practices farming and selling cereals as a business, which she has done for 18 years.

This is her second loan. She will use it to buy fertilizers to improve production and animal feeds for her cows. She will use the profits from this expanded business to buy food, clothes as well as pay school fees for her children.

Her hopes and dreams are to be financially stable and to be able to fully educate her children.
name: Alice
use: to buy fertilizers to improve production and animal feeds for her cows.

description.texts.en:
Christina is 45 years old, a married mother of 6 children. She is a service provider, she sews different clothes such as dresses, blouses, coats and trousers and has been running this business for 26 good years. She opens her business at 8:00 a.m and closes at 5:00 p.m daily. She earns a profit.

This will be Christina's 2nd loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She used her previous loan to buy a new sewing machine. She earned a profit that she used to support her family and reinvest in her business, thus managing to paying back the loan on time. She is applying for this loan to buy new fabrics and sewing materials to design different clothes to sell.

Her dreams is to open a new center for clothes sewing someday.

Christina will be responsible for paying back the loan.
name: Christina
use: to buy new fabrics and sewing materials to design different clothes to sell.

description.texts.en:
Caroline is a 47-year-old married woman with three children. Due to her experience, hardworking nature and commitment Caroline was nominated as the group leader for Trust And Obey Group.

Caroline has owned and operated a general retail business for the past 6 years. Like many of those in the group, her business is well organized and requires that she work from 8am to 7pm every day.

Despite the long days of work, Caroline is determined to operate a successful business in order to provide a better life for her family.

Caroline has requested a loan from Kiva through ID-Ghana in order to buy groceries like soap, sugar, juice, tea, oil, etc. With the profits from this loan, she will be able to reinvest in her business, pay school fees for her children, and save for her future.
name: Trust And Obey Group
use: to buy groceries like soap, sugar, juice, tea, oil, etc to sell.

description.texts.en:
When you take a glimpse of Lucy you will also confirm that she has a beautiful smile and she is very beautiful.

She is a middle-aged, inspiring farmer who lives in Nyahururu, in the central Province of Kenya. She has been identified as a very hardworking farmer, engaging in mixed farming, dairy, and poultry keeping.

Lucy is a mother who loves attending to her daily duties and making a living for her family. Lucy uses the few profits obtained from locally selling milk and eggs to pay for her children's school fees.

The quality of Lucy’s crops has dwindled due to the use of poor farm inputs. This has brought about low demand for her crops and has negatively impacted her sales.

Access to modern-quality farm inputs is the pillar of the agricultural revolution. However, in Kenya, a developing country, fertilizers and seed allocation by the government is way below the needs of farmers.

Lucy is on her knees humbly seeking a helping hand to purchase farming inputs such as fertilizers and hybrid seeds to boost the quality of her produce. Since Juhudi Kilimo, which is in partnership with Kiva, ventured into the affairs of smallholder farmers, farmers can attest that there has been a significant improvement in the availability of inputs.

Lucy is assured of a bumper harvest, which will open new markets for her crops and, subsequently, increase her profits. This will elevate her standard of living as well as that of her beautiful children.
name: Lucy
use: to purchase farming inputs such as fertilizers and hybrid seeds to boost the quality of her produce, earn more profits and elevate her living standards.

description.texts.en:
Ghati is 52 years old, a married mother of 3 boys and 3 girls who are still in school. She is a seller, she sells green bananas in the market and has been running this business for 10 good years now. She normally works from 6:00 a.m to 6:00 p.m daily to make a profit.

This will be Ghati's 2nd loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She used her previous loan to buy stock of green bananas to sell. She earned a good profit that she used to support her family's needs, and reinvesting in her business, she managed to pay back the loan.

She is applying for this loan to purchase more green bananas for her business to grow. Her dreams is to become a big business woman in the near future.

Ghati will be responsible for paying back the loan successfully.
name: Ghati
use: to purchase more green bananas for her business to grow.

description.texts.en:
The mom presented above is Alice. She is a woman who loves fashion. Thanks to her tirelessness and selflessness, Alice has managed to give her children a good foundation by providing them with a good quality education.

Alice hails from Bungoma, a remote area of Kenya. Her primary sources of income are maize crops and animal farming. Alice was born in a family where farming skills were passed from one generation to another. She did not have any other way of making an income so she chose to venture into farming. Through continuous involvement in crop and animal farming, Alice is able to provide a meal for her family at least once a day.

Alice has decided to focus more of her attention on farming. However, she needs to boost her income by buying different varieties of cereals (cow peas, lentils, maize) from local farmers and selling them to her customers and at the local market. Through this engagement, she will earn a commission that she intends to use to repay the loan and to elevate her standard of living. This loan is, therefore, an opportunity that she has never had before. Her irregular income and lack of collateral security were the main drawbacks limiting her from accessing a loan from commercial banks.

Thanks to Juhudi Kilimo and Kiva, the lives of Alice and her family will be changed through this loan.
name: Alice
use: to buy different varieties of cereals (cow peas, lentils, maize) from farmers and sell them to her customers, which will help to support her family and educate her children.

description.texts.en:
Get to know Beatrice, a beautiful mother who loves the color red and works on her mixed farm!

Converting her idea of starting a farm into a reality was the biggest achievement that she has ever made in her life. She started farming with the aim of supporting her children. She keeps cattle and poultry for milk and eggs, and grows vegetables. Her farming success was achieved through the fact that, among other things, she is very innovative and focused.

Access to modern-quality farm inputs is the pillar of the agricultural revolution. However in Kenya, a developing country, fertilizer and seed allocation by the government is way below the farmers' needs. Since Juhudi Kilimo, which is in partnership with Kiva, ventured into the affairs of smallholder farmers in Kenya, farmers can attest that there has been a significant improvement in input availability.

Beatrice is humbly seeking a loan to buy farm inputs such as seeds and hired labor in order to grow more crops, and then to use the profits from her farm to improve her children's living conditions. This intervention will help her to fill the increasing demand for food in the market and, in the process, generate more income to repay the loan debt and improve the quality of life for her family. She also hopes to improve the condition of her house.

Help this always-smiling and happy mother to accomplish all her dreams with a loan!
name: Beatrice
use: to buy farm inputs such as seeds and hired labor, in order to help a hardworking mother to grow more crops and use the profits from her farm to improve her living conditions.

description.texts.en:
?Neema is a 32-year-old, married mother of four school-going children. She is a retailer; she owns a retail shop where she sells different items such as food items, soft drinks and detergents. She has been in this business for 10 years. She normally opens her business from 6:00 am and closes at 7:30 pm daily. She earns a profit.

This will be Neema's second loan request from Tujijenge Tanzania. She purchased a few stationary items, food items, detergent and baby diapers with her previous loan. She earned a good profit that she used to support her family and reinvest in her business. She also managed to repay the loan. She is applying for this loan to buy more stock of different items such as maize flour, wheat flour, cooking oil, sugar, toothbrushes, detergents and other necessities. Her dream is to have a big business in the near future.

Neema will share a portion of this loan with her loan group members of Kimusi Grp Tarime.
name: Kimusi Grp Tarime-Unit Group

description.texts.en:
Stella is a practical woman. She has no higher education or work experience, only her wits and her desire to succeed in life. She is a very hardworking, progressive, and honest farmer from a very remote village in the Bungoma area of Kenya. This area is very fertile, with favorable weather patterns that support farming activities. Stella is happily married and the proud mother of a lovely family, and together they live on a small piece of land that she really treasures.

Her primary sources of income are crops, eggs, and milk.She is also a seamstress (pictured in her shop above). Although this humble and industrious mother makes a profit, she faces the challenge of not being able to produce enough to meet the ready market that is available. Therefore, she is seeking funds from Kiva lenders to buy farm inputs like good fertilizer and good quality seeds. Through this loan, she will double her production, and this will translate into increased income.

She then intends to save more money in the future so that she can develop her farming and also build a new, modern house. This loan will help Stella to realize her dream of getting out of poverty, and she will be able to secure her family's future.

Lenders, if there is someone that you should invest in, then that person is Stella. She will not let you down.
name: Stella
use: to buy farm inputs such as certified-quality seeds and fertilizer to improve her crop farming and eventually, through increased profits, improve her standard of living.
